In [19]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(25,15), sharex=True)

top_10_df = data[["date", "cmname"]].groupby("cmname").agg(['count'])["date"]['count'].sort_values(ascending=False)[:10]
fig = sns.barplot(x = top_10_df.index, y = top_10_df.values , ax=ax)
fig.set_ylabel("Number of records in the dataset")
fig.set_xlabel("food name")
fig.set_title("Top 10 price by mist data records")
Out[19]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Top 10 price by mist data records')
